    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect power correction factor in ULSCH demodulation\n\n### Summary\nThe `init_ulsch_power_LUT` function was initializing lookup table values that could cause downstream functions to receive incorrect parameters interpreted as flags or bitmasks. Specifically, `ulsch_power_LUT[0]` was set to 0, which when used in division operations could cause unexpected behavior in system functions.\n\nThis fix ensures all LUT values are at least 1 to prevent division by zero and related issues with flag/bitmask interpretation in downstream functions.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/ulsch_demodulation.c`: Modified `init_ulsch_power_LUT` to ensure all values are >= 1\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/transport_proto.h`: Added function declaration to eNB transport header\n- `openair1/PHY/INIT/lte_init.c`: Removed incorrect dependency on UE transport header\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain channel conditions, ULSCH power calculations would result in division by zero when `ulsch_power_LUT[0]` was accessed, causing incorrect power correction factors to be passed to signal processing functions. This manifested as erroneous SNR calculations and potential crashes in downstream signal processing functions that interpreted the invalid values as control flags.\n"
}